Nasarawa State Governor, Abdullahi Sule, yesterday said only God will decide who will be elected the All Progressives Congress (APC) national chairman between Senators Umaru Tanko Al-Makura and Abdullahi Adamu. He said he had no regrets supporting Al-Makura for the position, adding he would support Adamu if he wins. He urged supporters to be circumspect when commenting on the two Nasarawa prominent leaders’ aspirations. Sule spoke at the government when he received the report of the APC fact-finding and reconciliation committee.   Mustapha obtains nomination form for APC national chairman     Despite interests, APC still intact, says Sani Musa     Obiano takes final bow, Soludo steps in Thursday   “I have no regret whatsoever being able to say I am supporting Tanko Al-Makura. And I still support him. “But if God says it’s Adamu, he is also my father and our leader; I will give him all the maximum support. “It’s only God who will decide who is the leader of the party,” he said. The governor expressed satisfaction with the assignment undertaken by the committee chaired by Senator Salihu Agyegbola.